the 1-year peak).","dma":"price[t] / mean(price, last N days) - 1; 'above' = price >= the N-day average.","drawdown":"current = price[t]/running-peak - 1; maxDD = min(price/cummax - 1) over the window.","liquidity":"median daily traded value (turnover \u00f7 1e7 = \u20b9 cr) over the last ~21 trading days.","relative_strength":"horizon: stock return - benchmark return (pp); line: (stock/benchmark) rebased to 100 over the last year."},"notes":{"source":"adjusted total-return price panel (bhavcopy-reconstructed) + NSE index TR + bhavcopy turnover.","frequency":"daily","confidence":"high where history is long; flagged low if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":44.1,"unit":"/100","status":"weak","read":"Low-quality (44/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.14,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"weak","read":"Only 0.14\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.22,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.22\u00d7, interest cover 4.4\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-53.17,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 53% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":18.6,"pe_percentile":89.0,"median_pe":16.0,"earnings_yield_pct":5.38,"pb":1.04,"ev_ebitda":10.81,"quality_score":44.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":16.7,"peg":1.11,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 89-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 18.6\u00d7 earnings for ~17% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.11\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[59.38,59.38,59.38,59.38,59.38,59.38,59.38,59.39,59.4],"latest_pct":59.4,"chg_1y_pp":0.02},"FII":{"periods":["Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[4.72,3.14,0.05,0.14,0.05,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.19],"latest_pct":0.19,"chg_1y_pp":0.14},"DII":{"periods":["Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[3.27,1.82,1.41,1.41,1.3,1.3,1.24,1.24,1.24],"latest_pct":1.24,"chg_1y_pp":-0.06},"Public":{"periods":["Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[29.92,32.97,36.45,36.37,36.57,36.6,36.67,36.65,36.46],"latest_pct":36.46,"chg_1y_pp":-0.11}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"12-Sep-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting","materiality":"Med"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake up 0.02pp over ~1yr \u2192 59.40%.","FII":"FIIs adding (+0.14pp YoY \u2192 0.19%).","DII":"DIIs reducing (-0.06pp YoY \u2192 1.24%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"negative","score":-4,"drivers":["\u2212 Below its 200-day average (-32%) \u2014 downtrend.","\u00b7 50-day average still below the 200-day (no golden cross).","\u2212 60% below its 52-week high.","\u2212 Lagging the NIFTY 500 by -51pp over 12 months.","\u2212 In a deep drawdown (-73% from its peak)."],"rule":"Points: +1 price above its 200-day average \u00b7 +1 a golden cross (50-day \u2265 200-day) \u00b7 +1 within 10% of the 52-week high \u00b7 +1 beating the NIFTY 500 over 12 months; \u22121 for each opposite, and \u22121 if more than 25% below its peak. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less, otherwise neutral. The Market signals (above 200-DMA, golden cross, near 52-week high, beating the index) are CORRELATED facets of ONE trend, not independent confirmations \u2014 read the Market verdict as trend-strength, not a tally of independent votes."},"Business":{"verdict":"negative","score":-2,"drivers":["\u2212 Low-quality (44/100).","\u2212 Only 0.14\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","+ Conservatively financed (D/E 0.22\u00d7, interest cover 4.4\u00d7).","\u2212 Profit down 53% YoY (latest TTM)."],"rule":"Points across the four business flags: +1 for each that is 'good' (quality, cash conversion, balance-sheet safety, earnings momentum), \u22121 for each that is 'weak'. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less."},"Valuation":{"verdict":"negative","score":-2,"drivers":["\u2212 P/E at the 89-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."],"rule":"Cheap \u2014 P/E below the 30th percentile of its own 10-year range \u2014 scores +2 (supportive); expensive (above the 70th) scores \u22122; mid-range is 0. A peak/cyclical-earnings flag discounts a cheap read to +1. NOTE: 'positive' means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 it is NOT a buy call."},"Ownership":{"verdict":"positive","score":1,"drivers":["+ Promoter stake rising (+0.02pp YoY)."],"rule":"Points: +1 promoter stake rising \u00b7 \u22121 promoter stake falling more than 1pp in a year \u00b7 \u22121 promoter pledge above 10% \u00b7 +1 for each of FII / DII accumulating (>0.5pp in a year). Verdict: positive at +1 or more, negative at \u22121 or less."}},"top_positives":["Conservatively financed (D/E 0.22\u00d7, interest cover 4.4\u00d7).","Promoter stake rising (+0.02pp YoY)."],"key_risks":["Below its 200-day average (-32%) \u2014 downtrend.","60% below its 52-week high.","Lagging the NIFTY 500 by -51pp over 12 months.","In a deep drawdown (-73% from its peak).","Low-quality (44/100).","Only 0.14\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory)."],"monitor_next":["Next quarterly results (board-meeting date is an MVP-2 placeholder).","Re-rating toward / away from its median P/E (16.0\u00d7).","Relative-strength inflection vs its sector index.","Promoter pledge / institutional-holding changes next quarter."],"caveats":["Thinly traded \u2014 median ~\u20b90.20 cr/day (< \u20b91 cr); signals/exits may slip.","corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."],"confidence":"medium","disclaimer":"Diagnostics only \u2014 a structured reading of price behaviour, business fundamentals, valuation and ownership for your OWN judgement. This is NOT a buy/sell/hold recommendation.","method":"Each dimension is a transparent points tally of the named signals listed beneath it \u2014 open a dimension to see the exact signals that fired and its rule. Verdict = positive at +2 or more / negative at \u22122 or less for Market, Business and Valuation; \u00b11 for Ownership. A 'positive' valuation means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 never a buy call."},"data_quality":{"price_asof":"2026-06-30","fundamentals_fetched":"2026-06-20","has_fundamentals":true,"has_shareholding":true,"liquidity_warning":"Thinly traded \u2014 median ~\u20b90.20 cr/day (< \u20b91 cr); signals/exits may slip.","note":"Market data is daily and current; fundamentals & shareholding are as of the last cached Screener fetch (quarterly/annual). Confidence is lower for thin or short-history names."}}